&lt;&lt;4. This many years after the war, I doubt it is unlikely many of us will be convinced or have their opinions swayed by others to a new direction is unlikely. &gt;&gt;<br><br>
    I don't view this site--or any debate really--as an attempt to &quot;convert&quot; anyone but as an opportunity to see what other people are thinking. <br>
    Makes me thiink--and that's a good thing--for me.<br>
    If any of my comments have caused anyone else to think, then I've done what I set out to do.<br>
    While there are other &quot;supervised&quot; sites, this  unsensered/unfiltered serves a unique purpose that the other sites can/do not.  Students should be exsposed to all the forums rather then being restricted to only those that are &quot;approved.&quot;  <br>
   Smacks of Big Brotherism.  <br>
    Give them a list with your comments and turn them lose to use their--rather then your--minds to find &quot;the truth&quot; what ever the hell that is.<br>
     Skipping the emotions may be safer and more academiclly pure, but through out history--and today--more men have fought and died for emotional ideas then have done so for &quot;logical&quot; reasons.  Not a good critique on mankind perhaps, but true none-the-less.<br>
Good site.<br>
